                     <interp inst="def1-338-18481127" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES WELLS</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18481127-338-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18481127-338-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18481127-338-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="embezzlement"></interp> for embezzlement.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481127-name-734" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-734" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-734" type="surname" value="DOBSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-734" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH DOBSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a grocer. The prisoner was in my service—on 18th Nov. I watched him, and saw him put his hand into his waistcoat pocket—I went into the shop to speak to him, but returned, and saw him take half-a-crown from a customer—he gave the change—I then saw the half-crowu in</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184811270100"></xptr>
               <p>his hand—he did not put it into the till—I went towards him, and he dropped it behind him—he said, "It is only a weight, Sir; I will pick it up"—I said, "Come away from the counter"—I looked down, and found the half-crown.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PARNELL</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Who was in the shop? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> A good many customers—there were two persons to serve besides the prisoner—it was a little after eleven o'clock at night—I did not look into the till—I saw him throw the hall-crown on the counter, and go to the till to get change—I do not know what the customer bought—the prisoner was with me about eighteen months.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES GAIR</hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman A</hi> 447). I took the prisoner—he said, "Master, I am very sorry; I know I have done wrong; I hope you will forgive me this time."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> That was after some almonds were taken from his pocket? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes.</p>
               <p>
